Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.500 --> 00:00:04.180
&gt;&gt;COMMENTATOR: Hi everyone. Thanks for coming.

00:00:04.180 --> 00:00:05.890
It's great pleasure for me to introduce Tom
Bissell.

00:00:05.890 --> 00:00:13.809
Tom is the author of two previous books of
non-fiction: Chasing the Sea and The Father

00:00:13.809 --> 00:00:17.380
of All Things, as well as, the wonderful short
story collection God Lives in Saint Petersburg,

00:00:17.380 --> 00:00:18.640
which won him many well deserved accolades.

00:00:18.640 --> 00:00:21.029
In his newest book, Extra Lives, Tom shares
with us his long-time fascination with videogames.

00:00:21.029 --> 00:00:25.840
It's neither a history of the medium, nor
a survey of the industry, nor a technical

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:38.430
treatise on game design; but rather, it is
one man's opinions on what playing games feels

00:00:38.430 --> 00:00:45.070
like, an examination of why videogames matter,
and why they do not matter more.

00:00:45.070 --> 00:00:50.050
Whether or not you're already the gaming addict
that Tom reveals himself to be; Extra Lives

00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:54.410
provides a unique view of what these games
have become and makes a strong and provocative

00:00:54.410 --> 00:00:55.410
case for their continuing relevance and significance.

00:00:55.410 --> 00:00:57.570
Please join me in welcoming to YouTube, Tom
Bissell.

00:00:57.570 --> 00:00:58.570
