00:32:19.399 --> 00:32:20.399
Yes, sir.

00:32:20.399 --> 00:32:21.399
&gt;&gt;MAN FROM AUDIENCE: I'm curious to hear your
opinion on the kind of contemporary argument

00:32:21.399 --> 00:32:25.250
about what- what is the best use of tool or
combination of experiences for young adults.

00:32:25.250 --> 00:32:35.120
Obviously there is a role of videogame play
in the maturing of the young adults mind versus

00:32:35.120 --> 00:32:46.220
more active types of-of reading or other types
of intellectual stimulation. I'm just curious

00:32:46.220 --> 00:32:57.399
to hear your thoughts of how videogames play
in that whole developmental type of argument.

00:32:57.399 --> 00:33:04.360
&gt;&gt;TOM: Yeah, I would have to think based on
the little that I have read on the subject

00:33:04.360 --> 00:33:08.690
that I just can't imagine that a lot of videogame
playing is good for young adults. I just don't

00:33:08.690 --> 00:33:13.130
think it's probably very good for them, for
all sorts of reasons.

00:33:13.130 --> 00:33:14.130
[PAUSE]

00:33:14.130 --> 00:33:24.380
You know games should be a part of a rich,
cultural diet that people have. I mean, I

00:33:24.380 --> 00:33:27.610
grew up playing games and I also grew up a
huge reader. I don't think it's impossible.

00:33:27.610 --> 00:33:28.610
It's probably slightly more unusual.

00:33:28.610 --> 00:33:29.990
And as games-let's face it the games that
I played as a kid they weren't really--you

00:33:29.990 --> 00:33:33.360
couldn't really play them for more than a
couple of hours without going mad from boredom.

00:33:33.360 --> 00:33:36.730
Once you'd had Pitfall Harry go through the
