00:35:52.400 --> 00:35:57.580
 -- about that game; and I am really glad
that games don't do that anymore. I'm really,

00:35:57.580 --> 00:35:58.580
really, really glad.

00:35:58.580 --> 00:36:04.609
But it's very cool to play a game that occasionally
comes along and says, "Hey, you remember this

00:36:04.609 --> 00:36:05.810
style of game play [CHUCKLES]. We're going
to give it to you again."

00:36:05.810 --> 00:36:12.570
&gt;&gt;MAN FROM AUDIENCE: I mean do you think that
your enjoyment was partially this kinda throw

00:36:12.570 --> 00:36:17.830
back thing or do you think it was more that-that
there is genuinely something about that type

00:36:17.830 --> 00:36:18.830
of game that's...

00:36:18.830 --> 00:36:22.099
&gt;&gt;TOM: Well, it makes you very careful, and
it makes you very tense; and so, but tense

00:36:22.099 --> 00:36:29.710
in a way that -- like Resident Evil and Demon's
Souls are both fair. They don't like arbitrarily

00:36:29.710 --> 00:36:30.710
do stuff.

00:36:30.710 --> 00:36:35.440
They make you pay attention and they make
you really go slow and pay close watch on

00:36:35.440 --> 00:36:41.000
everything that is going on around you. And
as long as a game's fair about its sternness,

00:36:41.000 --> 00:36:43.170
I don't really have a quarrel with it.

00:36:43.170 --> 00:36:46.980
But, I think that a lot of the older games
were just hard for the sake of being hard.

00:36:46.980 --> 00:36:52.240
And they would throw these really arbitrary
kinds of things at you that were-that-that

00:36:52.240 --> 00:36:57.440
they weren't hard in a fun way; they weren't
hard in a way that rewarded paying close attention.

00:36:57.440 --> 00:37:01.420
And I think that's where a lot of game designers
kind of got hung up. They thought hardness

00:37:01.420 --> 00:37:07.690
was the thing to pursue rather than the encouragement
of paying attention. And those are two different

00:37:07.690 --> 00:37:10.420
qualities, I think.

00:37:10.420 --> 00:37:16.020
So. I will occasionally treat myself. And
most of the games that do that are Japanese.

00:37:16.020 --> 00:37:20.020
I mean, that-that's the Japanese style of
game design. They like hard games. They're

00:37:20.020 --> 00:37:21.020
into that.

00:37:21.020 --> 00:37:25.970
And western game designers moved away from
it, and I think that there is probably like

00:37:25.970 --> 00:37:29.850
a middle ground somewhere between the two.
'Cause there is something about a lot of games,

00:37:29.850 --> 00:37:30.850
a lot of them are pretty easy, you know.

00:37:30.850 --> 00:37:31.850
[PAUSE]

00:37:31.850 --> 00:37:37.420
But at the same time these guys want the games
to be more accessible and they want people

00:37:37.420 --> 00:37:42.890
to be able to enjoy them. You-you-you don't
feel like you are getting frustrated at this

00:37:42.890 --> 00:37:43.950
thing that you paid this money for.

00:37:43.950 --> 00:37:48.390
So I can see all sides of this argument simultaneously.
I don't really know if there is a right answer.

00:37:48.390 --> 00:37:54.270
I think it's just how the game approaches
it. 'Cause it is an aesthetic decision. And

00:37:54.270 --> 00:37:58.510
if it is an aesthetic decision that has like
a solid foundational grounding to it, then,

00:37:58.510 --> 00:38:02.060
I think if it is thoughtfully done; it's totally
legit any way you want to do it.

00:38:02.060 --> 00:38:03.060
[PAUSE]

00:38:03.060 --> 00:38:04.060
Ah, yes.

