00:41:57.079 --> 00:42:00.230
if you take away that ability that you can
kind of go back and change things, which seems

00:42:00.230 --> 00:42:01.800
like you have to do to get that resonance...

00:42:01.800 --> 00:42:02.800
&gt;&gt;TOM: Yeah.

00:42:02.800 --> 00:42:03.830
&gt;&gt;MAN IN AUDIENCE:...that's a game that not
a lot of people are even going to bother playing.

00:42:03.830 --> 00:42:04.830
&gt;&gt;TOM: Well...

00:42:04.830 --> 00:42:07.369
&gt;&gt;MAN IN AUDIENCE: I used to play Demon's
Souls. It's the game's impact -- enormous

00:42:07.369 --> 00:42:08.369
time

00:42:08.369 --> 00:42:09.369
&gt;&gt;TOM: [CHUCKLES]

00:42:09.369 --> 00:42:15.690
&gt;&gt;MAN IN AUDIENCE: Because everything is,
you know, so difficult, and your choices have

00:42:15.690 --> 00:42:16.690
such meaning.

00:42:16.690 --> 00:42:20.680
&gt;&gt;TOM: Yeah, I dont think it is the on...I
don't think irrevocability of that kind is,

00:42:20.680 --> 00:42:23.260
is not necessss...I mean, here's the thing.

00:42:23.260 --> 00:42:27.310
Yeah, as the game designer you can think well
people can just go back and reload it and

00:42:27.310 --> 00:42:28.310
experience it again.

00:42:28.310 --> 00:42:32.940
But when I play games, I-I don't do that.
I try to honor the vision of the designers,

00:42:32.940 --> 00:42:39.950
and I-I try to resist that game temptation
of just revisiting things that I did to see

00:42:39.950 --> 00:42:41.329
how they work out a different way.

00:42:41.329 --> 00:42:46.610
And so, I think game designers, in my opinion,
spend too much time anticipating the kid who

00:42:46.610 --> 00:42:52.780
wants to pee in the pool and-and figuring
out ways ta-ta-ta-to foil the kid who wants

00:42:52.780 --> 00:43:00.950
to pee in the pool. Thereby, and by doing
that they kind of make all the rest of us

00:43:00.950 --> 00:43:04.640
suffer through all the firewalls that they
are putting up around this kid. And I kind

00:43:04.640 --> 00:43:09.400
of think that if some people wanta break the
game, you can't really protect, you can't

00:43:09.400 --> 00:43:10.950
really worry about that.

00:43:10.950 --> 00:43:18.510
And so, I think all that you can do is just
design and encourage the player to sort of

00:43:18.510 --> 00:43:23.240
want to believe in the fictional primacy of
the world and not want you to violate it.

00:43:23.240 --> 00:43:28.460
And that's really the best you can do. And
you can just hope that people kinda go through

00:43:28.460 --> 00:43:32.150
with generally what you-you're trying to intend
them to experience.

00:43:32.150 --> 00:43:37.550
See you don't have to go the cruel Demon Souls
path. You can actually also take the s-somewhat

00:43:37.550 --> 00:43:43.520
gentler path and not-yeah-and not worry too
much about that thing. I mean, I don't know.

00:43:43.520 --> 00:43:48.230
I don't think there is a good answer to this
question, and I think that it's a kind of

00:43:48.230 --> 00:43:53.450
game-by-game issue that you have to approach.
So I hear you, that there doesn't seem to

00:43:53.450 --> 00:43:57.630
be a very satisfactory answer here, but I
do think that there are all sorts of kinds

00:43:57.630 --> 00:44:01.552
of resonances that are unique to games, and
those are the kinds of experiences that I

00:44:01.552 --> 00:44:02.552
love about games. And...

